Introduction

This report was created using the incarceration data set found online. This data set shows the incarceration rate over time between 1968 and 2018. It also shows us the population of each race as well as the jail population in each state as well as county. Down below I have created three different charts to show visualizations of black jail population, black vs white population in each county of Texas, and lastly a map that shows the percentage of latin people in each county of Texas.

Summary Information

In my data I tried to focus on race and population of different counties in Texas. Therefore I first looked for the state with the highest black jail population and after calculating it the state with the highest black jail population was California (summary_info$state_highest_black_jail_pop). Then I went on to see the county with the highest jail population in the state of Texas which was Harris County (summary_info$county_highest_jail_pop_in_TX). You can also see in my variable comparison chart that Harris County had the highest black population in Texas which makes sense that they also have the highest jail population. Furthermore I had also calculated the total population in Texas which came out to be 4698619 (summary_info$total_pop_in_TX). Lastly I also calculated the state and county with the highest fips which came out to be Weston County (summary_info$county_highest_fips) and Wyoming (summary_info$state_highest_fips). This makes sense because Weston County is a county in Wyoming.

Trends Chart

This chart below shows the top 10 unique counties in Texas every 5 years between 1990 and 2010. This shows us the black jail population over time throughout the years and as we can see from the chart Harris County and Dallas County had the highest black jail population between 1990 and 2010. You can see there is a huge difference between those two and the rest of the counties.

Variable comparison Chart

The comparison chart below shows the black and white population of 10 counties in Texas to shows the difference between the two races. As you can see the white population in each of these counties is significantly bigger than the black population. I included this chart to show maybe since the black population is very low then the black jail population might be low as well.

Map

The map below shows us the percentage of natives in each county of Texas. The places with lighter blue shows that the percentage of natives in those counties are higher compared to the places that are more darker. The darker places show the percentage of native population is very low. Throughout the entire map it shows the percentage of native population spread apart in the state of Texas.
